Collection is an interface in java which is implemented by List, Set and Map.

Please go through all the classes and interfaces which implement Collection.
The following is the link for java docs: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Collection.html

Whereas Collections is a proper class in java which consists of some famous predefined methods such as the 
sychronized method.
Please go through the following link for more details on the Collections class: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Collections.html



